<div class="SpellDiv" style="float:left; width:500px;">
<div class='heading'><P>Page-Bound Epiphany</p></div><P class='SPDet'><b>School</b> divination; <B>Level</b> bard 2, cleric/oracle 2, magus 2, sorcerer/wizard 2</p><div class='Sep1'>Casting</div><P class='SPDet'><b>Casting Time</b> 1 round</p><P class='SPDet'><b>Components</b> V, S, F (a book with blank pages)</p><div class='Sep1'>Effect</div><P class='SPDet'><b>Range</b> personal</p><P class='SPDet'><b>Duration</b> 1 round/level (see text)</p><P class='SPDet'><b>Saving Throw</b> none; <b>Spell Resistance</b> no</p><div class='Sep1'>Description</div><div class='SPDesc'><p>You magically scour the world's libraries for information that might refresh your memory about a topic. Upon casting this spell, the focus book's pages fill with snippets and selections from countless books. You can spend up to 1 round per caster level (maximum 10) reading these notes. You may cease reading at any time, and when you do you can immediately attempt one Knowledge check with a +1 circumstance bonus for each round you spent studying the book (maximum +10). The writing disappears when the spell ends, and if you fail to succeed at a Knowledge check on the round you stop reading the notes, you don't gain the benefits of this spell.</p></div>    
